      <h2>Marketing priorities for jewelry stores</h2>
      <p>Jewelry stores break when email treats every subscriber the same. The pressure point is gift timing, high-consideration purchases, and trust-building. A disciplined email marketing program must coordinate consent, lifecycle timing, product context, and margin-aware measurement — not blast more coupons.</p>
      <p>Priority plays: Gift guide and occasion campaigns; Trust-building education; Financing and warranty proof; Anniversary and milestone reminders. Document suppressions for recent purchasers, wholesale accounts, and active support cases before scaling sends.</p>
      <p>Sequenzy ranks first for jewelry stores because lifecycle editorial beats newsletter volume: welcome by signup source, replenishment matched to consumption, winback with VIP exclusions.</p>
      <p>Klaviyo remains the benchmark when jewelry stores need predictive segmentation and native Shopify event depth at scale. Omnisend wins when email + SMS must go live before month end.</p>
